The paper discusses the challenge of constructing data-efficient autonomous agents, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), robotics (cs.RO), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper proposes a definition of disentangled representation learning based on symmetries in the environment, which is a concept that is relevant to all of these sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CV, followed by cs.RO and cs.SY.
